## Error Prevention

### Common Mistakes to Avoid
- Using `{PLACEHOLDER}` instead of `$PLACEHOLDER` format
- Adding "neeto-" prefix to `$API_NAME_LOWER` values (should be just "cal", "desk", etc.)
- Missing openapi frontmatter in API reference pages
- Forgetting to update docs.json navigation when adding pages
- Not using bundled schema references (`/bundled/` instead of `/docs/`)
- Inconsistent file naming (not kebab-case)
- Missing SubdomainInfo import in API pages
- Wrong HTTP method in openapi frontmatter
- Not creating corresponding docs/*.yaml files for bundling
- Mixing placeholder formats in same project
- Forgetting to update .neetoci product configuration

### Quality Checklist
- [ ] All placeholders use `$PLACEHOLDER` format
- [ ] New API pages include openapi frontmatter with correct method/endpoint
- [ ] Navigation updated in docs.json with appropriate group and icon
- [ ] Schemas use common.yaml references where possible
- [ ] Code examples follow standard 4-language pattern (curl, JS, Python, PHP)
- [ ] File names use kebab-case consistently
- [ ] Titles use Title Case consistently
- [ ] SubdomainInfo imported in all API reference pages
- [ ] Bundle files created in docs/ directory
- [ ] OpenAPI references point to bundled files
- [ ] .neetoci configuration updated with correct product name
- [ ] Package.json uses neeto-$API_NAME_LOWER-api format
- [ ] docs.json blog URL uses neeto$API_NAME_LOWER format

### Validation Commands
```bash
# Check placeholder format consistency
grep -r "\{.*\}" . --include="*.mdx" --include="*.json" --include="*.yaml"

# Verify schema bundling setup
ls docs/*.yaml && ls bundled/*.yaml

# Check navigation completeness
jq '.navigation.pages[].pages[]' docs.json | sort
```

This assistant understands these patterns and will help maintain consistency across all Neeto API documentation while leveraging the existing Mintlify writing standards defined in writing-standards.mdc.
